		(uuid "6a896231-eae7-470d-a265-9a4105231323")
	)
	(text_box "The power status of each USB port can be determined by directly sensing the VBUS of J1 and J101 through simple resistor dividers into the 3.3 V domain. This approach avoids back-feeding risks, eliminates the need for open-collector pull-up handling, and provides an unambiguous indication of which USB port is present."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 28.702 65.278 0)
		(size 26.67 33.02)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "485d52ec-b149-4a44-a5ab-209473ea58a7")
	)
	(text_box "These NOTIFY signals are logic-only indicators and not analog measurements.\nThey will allow the RP2040 to determine which USB ports are being used."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
